The ucdual platform has the following configuration options:
DISABLE_SERIAL_RESET
You can disable the automatic serial reset by defining this
SERIAL_AUTOSTART
Defining this will turn on the serial stack at boot time. 
It consumes a lot of power (doesn't let the cpu to enter sleep/powersave modes)!
MIB_SERIAL
The default serial (PlatformSerial) will be on the 51 pin connector (you can use it on pc with a mib bridge)
instead of the USB
UCDUAL_REV
The ucdual revison you use, multiplied by 10. Known revisions (default is the highest):
2